BT /F2 20 Tf 54 742 Td (Custom Programming Language Interpreter in Java) Tj ET
BT /F1 13 Tf 54 710 Td (Demo Guide and Project Explanation) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 676 Td (1. Project Overview) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 658 Td (This project is a custom programming language interpreter built completely from scratch ) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 645 Td (in Java. The purpose is to understand how programming languages work internally, from ) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 632 Td (reading source code to executing output.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 611 Td (The project does not use parser generators such as ANTLR or JavaCC. Every major stage is) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 598 Td ( manually implemented using Java Standard Edition.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 569 Td (2. Main Pipeline) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 551 Td (The interpreter follows this complete flow:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.5 Tf 64 525 Td (Source Code) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.5 Tf 64 514 Td (-> Lexer) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.5 Tf 64 503 Td (-> Tokens) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.5 Tf 64 492 Td (-> Parser) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.5 Tf 64 481 Td (-> AST) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.5 Tf 64 470 Td (-> Interpreter) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.5 Tf 64 459 Td (-> Output) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 443 Td (This is called a tree-walking interpreter because the interpreter walks through the ) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 430 Td (Abstract Syntax Tree and executes each node.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 401 Td (3. Supported Language Features) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 383 Td (- Variable declarations using let) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 370 Td (- Variable assignment) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 357 Td (- Print statements) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 344 Td (- If / else conditions) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 331 Td (- While loops) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 318 Td (- For loops) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 305 Td (- Block statements with braces) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 292 Td (- Nested variable scopes) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 279 Td (- Numbers, strings, booleans, and null) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 266 Td (- Arithmetic operations: +, -, *, /) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 253 Td (- Comparison operations: >, >=, <, <=) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 240 Td (- Equality operations: ==, !=) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 227 Td (- Unary operations: ! and -) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 214 Td (- Line-number based lexer, parser, and runtime errors) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 201 Td (- Interactive terminal REPL and script-file execution) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 172 Td (4. Team Work Division) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 154 Td (- Person 1: Architecture, AST classes, and Environment) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 141 Td (- Person 2: Lexer and token generation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 128 Td (- Person 3: Parser and syntax analysis) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 115 Td (- Person 4: Interpreter and execution) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 94 Td (Each part connects to the next part through strict method signatures so the team can ) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 81 Td (work independently and still integrate cleanly.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 500 32 Td (Page 1 of 6) Tj ET
endstream
