BT /F2 13 Tf 54 592 Td (9. Operator Precedence) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 574 Td (The parser understands operator precedence. This means multiplication and division ) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 561 Td (happen before addition and subtraction.) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.5 Tf 64 535 Td (let x = 2 + 3 * 4;) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.5 Tf 64 524 Td (print x;) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 508 Td (The parser reads this as:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.5 Tf 64 482 Td (2 + \(3 * 4\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 466 Td (So the output is:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.5 Tf 64 440 Td (14) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 416 Td (10. For Loop Handling) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 398 Td (For loops are supported safely by converting them into existing block and while-loop AST) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 385 Td ( nodes. This avoids needing a separate ForStmt class.) Tj ET
