BT /F3 8.5 Tf 64 219 Td (    }) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.5 Tf 64 208 Td (}) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 184 Td (11. AST) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 166 Td (AST means Abstract Syntax Tree. It represents the structure of the program using Java ) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 153 Td (objects instead of raw text.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 132 Td (Expressions are represented by Expr nodes such as BinaryExpr, LiteralExpr, VariableExpr,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 119 Td ( AssignExpr, UnaryExpr, and GroupingExpr.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 98 Td (Statements are represented by Stmt nodes such as PrintStmt, VarDeclareStmt, IfStmt, ) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 85 Td (WhileStmt, BlockStmt, and ExpressionStmt.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 500 32 Td (Page 3 of 6) Tj ET
