BT /F2 13 Tf 54 606 Td (12. Visitor Pattern) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 588 Td (The project uses the Visitor Design Pattern. Each AST node has an accept method, and the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 575 Td ( interpreter implements visitor methods for each node type.) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.5 Tf 64 549 Td (visitBinaryExpr\(\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.5 Tf 64 538 Td (visitPrintStmt\(\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.5 Tf 64 527 Td (visitWhileStmt\(\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 511 Td (This keeps AST structure and execution logic cleanly separated.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 482 Td (13. Environment and Memory) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 464 Td (Environment.java manages variables and scoped memory. It stores variable names and ) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 451 Td (values in a map.) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.5 Tf 64 425 Td (Map<String, Object> values) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 409 Td (It also supports nested scopes using an enclosing Environment reference.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 388 Td (Example:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.5 Tf 64 362 Td (let value = 100;) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.5 Tf 64 351 Td ({) Tj ET
