BT /F2 13 Tf 54 617 Td (18. What To Say During Demo) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 599 Td (Our project is a custom interpreted language built from scratch in Java. The user writes) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 586 Td ( code in our language. First, the lexer breaks the code into tokens. Then the parser ) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 573 Td (checks the grammar and builds an AST. The AST represents the program structure. Finally,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 560 Td ( the interpreter walks the AST using the Visitor pattern and executes each statement. ) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 547 Td (Variables are stored in an Environment class, which supports nested scopes. This lets us) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 534 Td ( handle local and global variables properly.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 513 Td (The project does not rely on parser generators or external libraries. Everything is ) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 500 Td (implemented manually using Java Standard Edition.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 471 Td (19. Strengths) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 453 Td (- Built fully in Java) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 440 Td (- No external parser generator) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 427 Td (- Manual lexer) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 414 Td (- Manual recursive-descent parser) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 401 Td (- AST-based execution) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 388 Td (- Visitor design pattern) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 375 Td (- Nested environment for memory scope) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 362 Td (- Custom error handling) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 349 Td (- Line-number based errors) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 336 Td (- Interactive REPL support) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 323 Td (- Script file support) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 310 Td (- For loops implemented through while-loop conversion) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 281 Td (20. Limitations) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 263 Td (- No functions yet) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 250 Td (- No arrays yet) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 237 Td (- No classes yet) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 224 Td (- No input function yet) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 211 Td (- No break or continue yet) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 64 198 Td (- No advanced standard library yet) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 177 Td (These features can be added later because the project architecture is modular. We can ) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 164 Td (extend the lexer, parser, AST, and interpreter step by step.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 135 Td (21. Closing Line) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 117 Td (This project helped us understand how programming languages work internally, from source) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 104 Td ( code input to tokenization, parsing, AST construction, memory handling, and final ) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 91 Td (execution.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 500 32 Td (Page 6 of 6) Tj ET
endstream
